{{see|stød}}

==Old English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /sto:d/
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*stōdh-'', from Indo-European ''*sta-, *stə-'' ‘stand, set’.  Cognate with Old High German ''[[stuot]]'' (German ''[[Stute]]'' ‘mare’), Old Norse ''stóð'' (Swedish ''[[sto]]'' ‘mare’).  The IE root is also the source of Old Slavic ''[[stado]]''
===Noun===
'''stōd'''

# an enclosure for breeding horses
# a [[horse]] or [[horses]] used for breeding

===See also===
'''stōd''' ''verb form''
* first- or third-person singular preterite of [[standan]]

